<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-04-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-04-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="305" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">438.00/229: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-03T13:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 3,
                                        1923—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 2:43
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>47. Department is informed that the opinion of Judge Strong, legal
                            adviser, in which I concur, is that jurisdiction of Claims Commission
                                <pb facs="0527" n="403" xml:id="pg_403"/> is limited to pecuniary
                            claims pending on the date of the exchange of the ratifications of the
                            treaty, May 3, 1916.<note n="24" xml:id="d305fn24"><ref target="frus1916#pg_328"><hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 1916, p.
                                    328</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>